    <title>Bike to Work Act of 2017</title>
    <createDate>2017-05-20T03:11:40Z</createDate>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2017-05-31T16:48:24Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <actionDate>2017-05-19</actionDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Bike to Work Act of 201</strong><b>7</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to include a bicycle sharing system as a mass transit facility for purposes of the tax exclusion of employer-paid commuting expenses. The bill defines "bicycle sharing system" as a public transportation system: (1) consisting of a network of stations at which bicycles are made available to customers for commuting and short-term, point-to-point use within the network's service area; and (2) that is operated or authorized by a government agency or public-private partnership. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-05-19T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
